---
description: Data Fetching and State Management Strategy for Frontend UI
alwaysApply: false
globs: ["**/app/**/*.tsx", "**/components/**/*.tsx", "**/hooks/**/*.ts"]
---
<data-fetching-strategy>

<rules>
- Centralize API calls using customized fetch wrappers or API client utilities (e.g. `src/lib/api.ts`).
- Handle Authentication Tokens (JWT) transparently via HTTP interceptors or middleware.
- Prefer Server Actions for simple mutations and forms in Next.js App Router.
- For client-side data fetching, use SWR or React Query to handle caching, revalidation, and loading states.
- Implement unified error handling and loading skeletons (Suspense).
</rules>

</data-fetching-strategy>
